<item>
            <title>[BEAM-8579] Strip UTF-8 BOM bytes (if present) in TextSource.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BEAM-8579</link>
                <project id="12319527" key="BEAM">Beam</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TextSource in the org.apache.beam.sdk.io package can handle UTF-8 encoded files, and when the file contains byte order mark (BOM), it will preserve it in the output. According to Unicode standard (&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode5.0.0/ch02.pdf&amp;amp;sa=D&amp;amp;usg=AFQjCNF_PW0McUUnM1UrvZSIwgvAj1uUKw&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode5.0.0/ch02.pdf&lt;/a&gt;): &quot;Use of a BOM is neither required nor recommended for UTF-8&quot;. UTF-8 with a BOM will also be a potential problem for some Java implementations (e.g.,&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.google.com/url?q=https://bugs.java.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id%3D4508058&amp;amp;sa=D&amp;amp;usg=AFQjCNEdT7vUK99N5bxQc9fkCt-uIG2v7Q&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://bugs.java.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=4508058&lt;/a&gt;). As a general practice, it&apos;s suggested to use UTF-8 without BOM.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Proposal: remove BOM bytes in the output from TextSource.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
